trace.verification_evidence:
{
  "red_failure_evidence": "BEFORE THIS CELL: the port could create a plain shell tab (landed one cell earlier) but had no way to start an agent — git show HEAD:src/herdr/mod.rs shows a trait with snapshot, ping, read_pane, send_input, send_keys and tab_create, and nothing that spawns an agent. wire::Agent had no name field at all (pane_id, workspace_id, tab_id, kind, status, title), so herdr's agent name reached the gateway and was dropped on the floor: nothing in the codebase could tell one agent from another by name, which is what an auto-generated-name-with-retry scheme depends on. PRE-CHANGE CHECK THAT FAILED: cargo test --quiet --lib -- agentstart_ | grep -qE 'test result: ok. ([6-9]|[1-9][0-9]+) passed' on the untouched tree printed 'running 0 tests / test result: ok. 0 passed; 186 filtered out' and the guard grep exited 1 — no test carrying the agentstart_ prefix existed. Two further reds were recorded during orchestrator review: the fake gave a freshly started agent AgentStatus::Unknown, a status the app's own spec defines as 'herdr reported a value this app doesn't recognize', which a just-spawned agent is not; and the fake fabricated a tab id when the workspace had no active tab, producing a pane pointing at a tab absent from snap.tabs — a shape real herdr cannot emit.",
  "green_evidence": {
    "command": "cargo test --quiet && cargo fmt --all --check && cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings && cargo test --lib -- agentstart_ | grep -qE 'test result: ok. ([6-9]|[1-9][0-9]+) passed'",
    "run_by": "orchestrator, independently, after the worker reported",
    "output": "cargo test --quiet: 201 passed, 0 failed (186 before this cell). fmt --all --check: silent. clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings: silent. agentstart_-only: test result: ok. 15 passed; 0 failed; 186 filtered out. Guard grep exit code: 0."
  },
  "behavior_change_description": "agent_start landed on the trait, SocketHerdr and FakeHerdr, and wire::Agent gained the name field at all three population sites. The socket call sends exactly name, argv, cwd, workspace_id and focus:false, and deliberately omits tab_id and split so upstream's own placement (split off the workspace's active tab) applies and agent_placement_conflict cannot arise. The name-collision retry is owned by the port, not its callers: generate, call, and on AgentNameTaken regenerate and retry, bounded at five attempts with a terminal error naming the exhaustion. The fake genuinely starts: it appends the Agent carrying the requested name, the Pane with the requested cwd, and a screens entry so the pane is immediately readable, checking collisions against its own snapshot rather than side-state.",
  "observable_difference": "A caller can now start a named agent in a chosen workspace and read its pane, and a name collision resolves itself invisibly instead of surfacing. Before, no such call existed and the agent name was not even parsed.",
  "regression_guard": "15 agentstart_ tests. agentstart_retries_once_then_succeeds and agentstart_gives_up_after_five_collisions pin both ends of the retry bound; agentstart_params_omit_tab_id_and_split pins the deliberate omission that keeps agent_placement_conflict unreachable; agentstart_wire_agent_parses_name_field and agentstart_wire_agent_name_defaults_empty_when_absent guard the widened wire type in both directions; agentstart_no_active_tab_errors_without_inventing_one asserts both the agent_placement_not_found result and that a failed placement leaves the snapshot untouched — no agent, no pane, no screen.",
  "reviewer_note": "Three rounds of orchestrator review. (1) The fake gave a fresh agent AgentStatus::Unknown; the app's spec reserves unknown for a value it failed to understand, so this asserted something false and would have shown an UNKNOWN badge on a just-created agent in demo mode — changed to Idle. (2) The fake fabricated a tab id via unwrap_or_else when the workspace had no active tab, attaching the new agent and pane to a tab that need not exist; replaced with the agent_placement_not_found result herdr itself uses, riding as Remote since the variant set is closed. (3) That placement guard shipped with no test covering it; a test was required and added, asserting the failure path mutates nothing."
}
